ğŸŒ TCP 3-Way Handshake (Detailed Explanation)
ğŸ”¹ What is it?

        TCP ek reliable protocol hai (matlab data galat na ho, missing na ho, sahi order me mile).
        Connection banane ke liye TCP ek process use karta hai = 3-Way Handshake.
        ğŸ‘‰ Ye process ensure karta hai ki Client aur Server dono ready hai communicate karne ke liye.

ğŸ“Œ Steps of TCP 3-Way Handshake
ğŸŸ¢ Step 1: SYN (Synchronize)

        Client â†’ Server
        
        Client bolta hai:
        ğŸ‘‰ "Hello Server, main connection banana chahta hoon, aur mera sequence number yeh hai (ex: 1000)."

Technical:

        TCP header me SYN flag = 1 hota hai.
        
        Client apna ek random Initial Sequence Number (ISN) bhejta hai.

ğŸŸ¡ Step 2: SYN + ACK (Synchronize + Acknowledge)

        Server â†’ Client
        
        Server bolta hai:
        ğŸ‘‰ "Hello Client, mujhe tumhara message mila (ACK), aur main bhi ready hoon, mera sequence number yeh hai (ex: 5000)."

Technical:

        Server ACK bhejta hai to confirm kare ki usne client ka SYN receive kiya.
        
        Server apna bhi SYN bhejta hai (apna ISN).
        
        Matlab ek hi packet me SYN + ACK flags = 1 hote hain.

ğŸ”µ Step 3: ACK (Acknowledge)

        Client â†’ Server
        
        Client bolta hai:
        ğŸ‘‰ "Ok Server, mujhe tumhara bhi message clear mila, ab hum data bhejna start karte hain."

Technical:

        Client ACK bhejta hai server ke SYN ke liye.
        
        Ab dono side ke sequence numbers confirm ho gaye.
        
        âœ… Ab connection establish ho gaya!
        Dono taraf ab Data Transmission shuru ho sakta hai.

ğŸ¯ Example with Phone Call ğŸ“

        Client (Tu): "Hello, Sun rahe ho?" (SYN)
        
        Server (Dost): "Haan, main sun raha hoon. Tum sun rahe ho?" (SYN + ACK)
        
        Client (Tu): "Haan, sun raha hoon. Chalo baat shuru karein." (ACK)
        â¡ï¸ Ab call connected. Tum dono baat (data exchange) kar sakte ho.

ğŸ”‘ Why 3-Way?

        SYN: Client ready hone ka signal deta hai.
        
        SYN + ACK: Server apna readiness + client ke message ka confirmation deta hai.
        
        ACK: Client final confirm deta hai.

ğŸ‘‰ Ye 3 steps se dono taraf ka sync aur confirmation ho jata hai.

ğŸ“ Key Points to Remember:(Shortcut)

        TCP reliable hai (har packet acknowledge hota hai).
        
        Handshake me 3 packets exchange hote hain.
        
        Is process ke baad hi data transfer start hota hai.
        
        Har side apna Sequence Number exchange karti hai.

Agar beech me koi step fail ho jaye â†’ connection establish nahi hota.
